My husband and I were in this restaurant on October 5, 2019 at 6:46 PM (as per picture of the detailed bill) The food was very good. However when we got the bill was a NON-CASH ADJ for $6.36. I asked to speak with the manager because this is not right to conduct business. The manager said that this is the new policy. I told that it is not right, that this means they are trying to not pay taxes. Did not work. I paid the bill with credit card. I am against of cash payments because of taxes. I signed the credit card receipt and I noticed that I did not have my detailed bill attached to my credit card receipt. I detached the detailed bill from the merchant copy and the waiter told me that the bill belongs to the restaurant. I requested my copy. The waiter said that was the restaurant policy. I took a picture of the bill and will report to the NY office and the credit bureau.  This is not acceptable. For my understanding this is a clear indication of tax invasion.

I had a nearly flawless experience at Chadwicks. It had been recommended to me by several folks and I finally tried it, and will certainly return.  9PM and got seated for two immediately, and was given a choice between two tables. It was very clean and well lit (although not overly bright), quiet, and smelled delicious. The tables are not as close together as many places, it feels spacious and comfortable.  I had lobster bisque, an iceberg and gorgonzola salad, and a medium rare filet mignon. The steak was served with grilled asparagus and whipped potatoes, with a yummy bacon tomato jam. Everything was fantastic, I have zero complaints about the food. In fact I over ate a little, because it was so good I couldn't help myself.  The service was also exemplary. Our server was friendly and polite, knew all the specials in great detail, and frequently checked in with us to make sure everything was good. It was also very quick...we sat down at 9PM and were ready to leave shortly after 10.  I'm looking forward to going back for more. Definitely one of the best places I've been to in Bay Ridge. Highly recommend Chadwicks.
